283	Cantaloupe Bread with Praline Glaze	15 mins	1 hrs 5 mins	2 hrs 20 mins	20	2 9x5-inch loaves	2 cups white sugar, 2 cups cantaloupe - peeled, seeded and pureed, 1 cup vegetable oil, 3 large eggs, 1 tablespoon vanilla extract, 3 cups all-purpose flour, 2 teaspoons ground cinnamon, 1 teaspoon baking soda, 1 teaspoon salt, ¾ teaspoon baking powder, ½ teaspoon ground ginger	Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Lightly grease and flour two 9x5-inch loaf pans.\nBeat together sugar, puréed cantaloupe, oil, eggs, and vanilla in a large bowl until well combined. Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, baking powder, and ginger in a separate bowl. Stir flour mixture into cantaloupe mixture until combined. Divide batter evenly between the prepared pans.\nBake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the centers of loaves comes out clean, about 1 hour.\nMeanwhile, make sauce: Combine brown sugar and butter in a microwave-safe bowl. Cook in the microwave for 3 minutes, stirring at 1-minute intervals. Mix in pecans.\nPour sauce over warm loaves. Let cool for 1 hour before serving.	4.5	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/22309/cantaloupe-bread-with-praline-glaze/	/Bread/Quick Bread Recipes/Fruit Bread Recipes/	Total Fat 18g 24%, Saturated Fat 5g 26%, Cholesterol 40mg 13%, Sodium 242mg 11%, Total Carbohydrate 48g 18%, Dietary Fiber 1g 4%, Total Sugars 33g, Protein 3g, Vitamin C 6mg 29%, Calcium 32mg 2%, Iron 1mg 7%, Potassium 103mg 2%	Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 1 hrs 5 mins, Additional Time: 1 hrs, Total Time: 2 hrs 20 mins, Servings: 20, Yield: 2 9x5-inch loaves	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/7SRda0dZW21XGekNnDYaYYbjpXU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Cantaloupe-Bread-with-Praline-Glaze-Tammy-Lynn-2000-ad6e8c4e6811469280837ff6378629a4.jpg
