285	Cantaloupe Pie I	30 mins	1 hrs	1 hrs 30 mins	8	1 to 9 - inch pie	1  cantaloupe, ½ cup white sugar, 8 tablespoons all-purpose flour, ¼ teaspoon salt, 3  egg yolks, 2 tablespoons water, 1 tablespoon butter, ¼ teaspoon butter flavored extract, 3  egg whites, ¼ teaspoon cream of tartar, 6 tablespoons white sugar, 1 (9 inch) pie crust, baked	Select a cantaloupe of good quality. Cut in half, remove seeds, and scoop pulp into a saucepan. Place pulp over medium heat until it comes to a gentle boil. Mash the cantaloupe as it heats. This should make about 2 cups of pulp.\nCombine 1/2 cup sugar, flour, and salt. Add to heated cantaloupe and cook, stirring, until thick. The amount of flour seems large, but it takes considerable thickening to obtain correct consistency.\nIn a large bowl, beat egg yolks; add water to yolks. Add a little of the cantaloupe mixture to egg yolks in order to heat yolks gradually. Stir egg yolks mixture into cantaloupe mixture. Continue cooking, stirring, until thick and creamy. Remove from heat.\nAdd butter or margarine and flavoring to the cantaloupe mixture.\nPour into baked pie shell.\nBeat egg whites and cream of tartar together until frothy. Continue beating, adding the 6 tablespoons sugar gradually; beat until thick peaks form. Top the pie with this meringue.\nBake at 400 degrees F (205 degrees C) until delicately brown on top.	4.3	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/12098/cantaloupe-pie-i/	/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/	Total Fat 9g 11%, Saturated Fat 3g 16%, Cholesterol 81mg 27%, Sodium 220mg 10%, Total Carbohydrate 42g 15%, Dietary Fiber 1g 3%, Total Sugars 28g, Protein 4g, Vitamin C 25mg 127%, Calcium 20mg 2%, Iron 1mg 6%, Potassium 254mg 5%	Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 1 hrs, Total Time: 1 hrs 30 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 to 9 - inch pie	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/4ysFi94Gbh3TCwsiXTv-RFHNnvM=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/5605391-f3b5c45dbc854872b8832d27f0389ab7.jpg
