364	Award Winning Peaches and Cream Pie	30 mins	40 mins	3 hrs 30 mins	8	1 to 10 - inch pie	¾ cup all-purpose flour, ½ teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 (3 ounce) package non-instant vanilla pudding mix, 3 tablespoons butter, softened, 1  egg, ½ cup milk, 1 (29 ounce) can sliced peaches, drained and syrup reserved, 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, softened, ½ cup white sugar, 1 tablespoon white sugar, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon	Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease sides and bottom of a 10 inch deep-dish pie pan.\nIn a medium mixing bowl, mix together flour, salt, baking powder and pudding mix. Mix in butter, egg and milk. Beat for 2 minutes. Pour mixture into pie pan. Arrange the peach slices on top of the pudding mixture.\nIn a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach syrup. Beat for 2 minutes. Spoon mixture over peaches to within 1 inch of pan edge. Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, and sprinkle over top.\nBake in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown. Chill before serving.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n	4.5	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/15142/award-winning-peaches-and-cream-pie/	/Desserts/Pies/Fruit Pies/Peach Pie Recipes/	Total Fat 15g 19%, Saturated Fat 9g 47%, Cholesterol 67mg 22%, Sodium 422mg 18%, Total Carbohydrate 54g 20%, Dietary Fiber 1g 5%, Total Sugars 42g, Protein 6g, Vitamin C 1mg 5%, Calcium 84mg 6%, Iron 1mg 6%, Potassium 169mg 4%	Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 40 mins, Additional Time: 2 hrs 20 mins, Total Time: 3 hrs 30 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 to 10 - inch pie	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/WENukrI_dVPBvq-ub0NaJa3MaFc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/4120799-b6fd33463e1a49d4954e30bcf674f4d1.jpg
365	Peaches and Cream, Literally	10 mins	10 mins	3 hrs 20 mins	4	4 servings	4  fresh peaches, or as needed, ⅓ cup white sugar, or to taste, ¼ cup water, 1 ½ cups heavy cream	Cut each peach in half along the crease, twist open, and remove the pit. Peel and slice. Cut slices in half to get roughly 2 cups of sliced peaches.\nBring sugar and water to a boil in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Boil until a syrup forms, about 3 minutes. Stir in peaches until coated. Bring syrup back to a light simmer, about 1 minute. Immediately remove from heat and pour mixture into a bowl.\nTransfer peaches into a large bowl using a slotted spoon. Pour in heavy cream and stir to combine. Divide mixture between serving glasses, cover with plastic wrap, and refrigerate until completely chilled and cream has absorbed all the peach flavor, at least 3 hours.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nChef John\n	4.6	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/274821/peaches-and-cream-literally/	/Desserts/Fruit Desserts/Peach Dessert Recipes/	Total Fat 33g 42%, Saturated Fat 21g 103%, Cholesterol 122mg 41%, Sodium 38mg 2%, Total Carbohydrate 25g 9%, Total Sugars 23g, Protein 2g, Vitamin C 42mg 212%, Calcium 70mg 5%, Iron 0mg 1%, Potassium 100mg 2%	Prep Time: 10 mins, Cook Time: 10 mins, Additional Time: 3 hrs, Total Time: 3 hrs 20 mins, Servings: 4, Yield: 4 servings	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/_qv4Cr4VDpmYdEzh8uEF4wBUIrU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/6864209-peaches-and-cream-literally-Chef-John-1x1-1-885400a0b094497a8fe7a7ed139f21c6.jpg
366	Nana's Southern Pickled Peaches	30 mins	40 mins	13 hrs 10 mins	40	5 quarts	4 cups white sugar, 1 cup white vinegar, 1 cup water, 2 tablespoons whole cloves, 4 pounds fresh clingstone peaches, blanched and peeled , 5 (3 inch) cinnamon sticks	Inspect 5 quart-sized jars for cracks and rings for rust, discarding any defective ones. Immerse in simmering water until peaches are ready. Wash new, unused lids and rings in warm soapy water.\nAt the same time, combine sugar, vinegar and water in a large pot, bring to a boil. Boil until syrupy, about 5 minutes.\nWhile the sugar mixture is boiling, press 1 to 2 cloves into each peach.\nPlace peaches into the boiling syrup. Boil until peaches are tender, about 20 minutes.\nSpoon peaches into hot, sterilized jars, and top with liquid, filling to within 1/2 inch of the rim. Insert a cinnamon stick in each jar. Wipe the rims with a clean dry cloth, and seal with lids and rings.\nPlace a rack in the bottom of a large stockpot and fill halfway with water. Bring to a boil and lower jars 2 inches apart into the boiling water using a holder. Pour in more boiling water to cover jars by at least 1 inch. Bring to a rolling boil, cover, and process for 10 minutes to seal, or consult times recommended by your local extension.\nRemove the jars from the stockpot and let rest, several inches apart, for 12 to 24 hours. Press the center of each lid with a finger to ensure the lid does not move up or down. Remove the rings for storage and store in a cool, dark area.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAmbria_red\n	4.9	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/72126/nanas-southern-pickled-peaches/	/Side Dish/Sauces and Condiments/	Sodium 2mg 0%, Total Carbohydrate 23g 8%, Dietary Fiber 0g 1%, Protein 0g, Vitamin C 15mg 73%, Calcium 11mg 1%, Iron 0mg 1%, Potassium 14mg 0%	Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 40 mins, Additional Time: 12 hrs, Total Time: 13 hrs 10 mins, Servings: 40, Yield: 5 quarts	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/Q7lR_HiK9TUrsxzSEvyQ5nfz1yE=/1500x0/filters