370	Butter Biscuit Peach Cobbler	15 mins	1 hrs	1 hrs 35 mins	10	10 servings	2 (29 ounce) cans peaches, ¾ cup white sugar, ½ cup brown sugar, ½ cup unsalted butter, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon, ½ teaspoon nutmeg, 1 pinch salt, 1 (16 ounce) can refrigerated buttermilk biscuit dough (such as Pillsbury Grands!®), 1 pinch ground cinnamon, 1 pinch white sugar, 1 pinch ground nutmeg, 1  pastry for a 9-inch pie crust	Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).\nMix peaches, 3/4 cup white sugar, brown sugar, butter, cornstarch, vanilla extract, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, and salt in a large pot over medium heat; cook and stir until sugars are dissolved and butter is melted, about 5 minutes.\nSprinkle each biscuit with 1 pinch cinnamon, 1 pinch white sugar, and 1 pinch nutmeg. Flatten biscuits on a lightly floured surface using a rolling pin. Cut each flattened biscuit into 12 to 15 small squares; stir into peach mixture. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 10 minutes.\nPour peach-biscuit mixture into a 9x13-inch baking dish and allow to thicken for 2 to 3 minutes; cover or decorate with pie crust. Cover dish with a sheet of aluminum foil and place dish on a baking sheet.\nBake in the preheated oven until crust is golden brown, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool before serving.	4.6	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/234306/butter-biscuit-peach-cobbler/	/Desserts/Fruit Desserts/Peach Dessert Recipes/	Total Fat 21g 27%, Saturated Fat 9g 45%, Cholesterol 25mg 8%, Sodium 552mg 24%, Total Carbohydrate 73g 27%, Dietary Fiber 3g 12%, Total Sugars 46g, Protein 5g, Vitamin C 6mg 30%, Calcium 50mg 4%, Iron 2mg 12%, Potassium 313mg 7%	Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 1 hrs, Additional Time: 20 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 35 mins, Servings: 10, Yield: 10 servings	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/-vsGcpSFYl0IRhPyp8acS_HQcWE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/856891