455	My Mother-in-Law's Plum Bread	15 mins	45 mins	1 hrs 10 mins	8	1 9x5-inch loaf	1 cup pitted, chopped plums, 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour, ½ cup margarine, 1 cup white sugar, ½ teaspoon vanilla extract, 2  eggs, 1 ½ cups all-purpose flour, ½ teaspoon salt, ¼ teaspoon baking soda, ⅓ cup plain yogurt, ¼ cup brown sugar	Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 9x5-inch loaf pan with cooking spray, or line with parchment paper.\nSprinkle chopped plums with 1 tablespoon of flour in a bowl, and toss to coat. Set aside. In a large bowl, beat the margarine, white sugar, and vanilla extract with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs. In another bowl, sift together 1 1/2 cup of flour with salt and baking soda. Stir the dry ingredients into the egg mixture, alternating with yogurt until the mixture forms a smooth batter. Lightly stir in the flour-coated plums, and pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan. Sprinkle the top of the batter with brown sugar.\nBake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the loaf comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes. Remove from oven, and let cool in the pan 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan for slicing.	4.8	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/215130/my-mother-in-laws-plum-bread/	/Bread/Quick Bread Recipes/Fruit Bread Recipes/	Total Fat 13g 17%, Saturated Fat 3g 13%, Cholesterol 47mg 16%, Sodium 343mg 15%, Total Carbohydrate 51g 19%, Dietary Fiber 1g 3%, Total Sugars 33g, Protein 5g, Vitamin C 2mg 11%, Calcium 39mg 3%, Iron 1mg 8%, Potassium 112mg 2%	Prep Time: 15 mins, Cook Time: 45 mins, Additional Time: 10 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 10 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 1 9x5-inch loaf	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/1MOQ_bXEjlW-Sp_zNHomKuSBSpc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/2507917-my-mother-in-laws-plum-bread-SherYum-4x3-1-ecb98977df3041aa9ab294e5b9786fbd.jpg
