825	Mexican Chicken and Rice Soup (Sopa de Pollo y Arroz)	25 mins	45 mins	1 hrs 10 mins	8	8 servings	2 ½ quarts chicken stock, 2 pounds skin-on, bone-in whole chicken legs (drumsticks and thighs), 3  carrots, chopped, 1  white onion, chopped, 2 stalks celery, chopped, ¼ cup chopped fresh cilantro, 1 clove garlic, 1 tablespoon chopped fresh mint,   salt and ground black pepper to taste, 3 cups cooked rice, 1  avocado, peeled and chopped, 2  serrano peppers, minced, 2  limes, quartered	Bring stock to a boil in a large pot over high heat. Add chicken legs; return to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 10 minutes, skimming away foam that forms on the surface. Add carrots, onion, celery, cilantro, garlic, and mint.\nCover pot and cook until chicken is no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 30 minutes more. Remove chicken from the pot; discard skin and bones. Shred meat using 2 forks.\nReturn chicken meat to the pot and season with salt and pepper. Add rice. Let chicken and rice warm up, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and pour soup into serving bowls. Top with avocado and serrano peppers and squeeze in lime juice.	5.0	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/262306/mexican-chicken-and-rice-soup-sopa-de-pollo-y-arroz/	/Soups, Stews and Chili Recipes/Soup Recipes/Chicken Soup Recipes/	Total Fat 15g 19%, Saturated Fat 4g 18%, Cholesterol 65mg 22%, Sodium 957mg 42%, Total Carbohydrate 26g 10%, Dietary Fiber 4g 13%, Total Sugars 3g, Protein 22g, Vitamin C 12mg 59%, Calcium 49mg 4%, Iron 2mg 12%, Potassium 450mg 10%	Prep Time: 25 mins, Cook Time: 45 mins, Total Time: 1 hrs 10 mins, Servings: 8, Yield: 8 servings	https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/eF1fHellBrcbGWJ_Pv-YJbZigLI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/5013253-9fe61539870347b6b02da102ec904a5e.jpg
