891	Great-Grandmother Bubbie's Hamantaschen	20 mins	30 mins	2 hrs 50 mins	36	3 dozen	2 cups pitted prunes, cooked, drained and mashed, 2 cups dried apricots, cooked drained and mashed, 3  eggs, 1 cup white sugar, ½ cup safflower oil, 1  lemon, zested, 1  orange, zested, 4 cups unbleached all-purpose flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, ½ cup chopped walnuts, ⅓ cup white sugar, or to taste	Place prunes and apricots into a large pot filled with water and bring to a rolling boil over high heat. Cook the fruit uncovered, stirring occasionally, until the fruit is tender, about 15 minutes. Drain fruit in a colander and mash together in a bowl using a fork. Set aside.\nPreheat an oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).\nWhisk eggs, 1 cup sugar, oil, lemon zest, and orange zest together in a bowl and set aside. Sift flour and baking powder together in a large bowl. Stir in the egg mixture, kneading with hands until the dough comes together. Roll out dough to about 1/4 inch in thickness on a lightly floured surface. Cut circles out using a cookie cutter or the rim of a drinking glass.\nMix prune and apricot mixture, lemon juice, walnuts, and 1/3 cup sugar in a bowl. Place a tablespoon of the filling in the center of the cookie. Pinch the edges firmly together to create a triangle, leaving the center open to expose the filling. Repeat with the remaining cookies.\nBake in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Cool in the pans for 10 minutes before removing to cool completely on a wire rack.	4.5	https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/191359/great-grandmother-bubbies-hamantaschen/	/Desserts/Cookies/Fruit Cookie Recipes/Apricot/	Total Fat 5g 6%, Saturated Fat 0g 2%, Cholesterol 16mg 5%, Sodium 34mg 1%, Total Carbohydrate 29g 11%, Dietary Fiber 2g 6%, Total Sugars 15g, Protein 3g, Vitamin C 1mg 5%, Calcium 30mg 2%, Iron 1mg 7%, Potassium 183mg 4%	Prep Time: 20 mins, Cook Time: 30 mins, Additional Time: 2 hrs, Total Time: 2 hrs 50 mins, Servings: